Emergency paramedics wearing a full COVID-19 coronavirus personal protective equipment (PPE) transfer an empty gurney to an ambulance at the Greenacres Hospital in Port Elizabeth, on July 10, 2020. JOHANNESBURG - South Africa's COVID-19 cases have passed the half-a-million mark. The health department recorded more than 10,000 new infections in the last 24 hours, taking the cumulative total of COVID-19 cases to 503, 290. READ: COVID-19: Expect 'lengthy' pandemic WHO warns The department also recorded 148 more deaths, bringing the death toll to 8153. Most of the new deaths were recorded in KZN and Gauteng. More than 342,000 people have recovered from the virus. Health Media Release 1 August 2020 2 by eNCA.com on Scribd 